## Quick Reference

### Core Workflow

**`sc kanban`** - Kanban task management system
  Options: `--filter <type>`, `--priority <level>`
  Example: `sc kanban list`

**`sc validate`** - Validate project structure and requirements
  Options: `--requirements`, `--tests`
  Example: `sc validate --all`

**`sc priority`** - Priority management for requirements and tasks
  Options: `--file <file>`, `--dry-run`
  Example: `sc priority --help`

### Development

**`sc generate`** - Generate project files and documentation
  Options: `--templates`, `--docs`
  Example: `sc generate --help`

**`sc docs`** - Documentation management system
  Options: `--format <format>`, `--output <path>`
  Example: `sc docs --help`

**`sc dev`** - Development tools and utilities
  Options: `--max-ratio <ratio>`, `--output <file>`
  Example: `sc dev --help`

### System Management

**`sc install`** - Install supernal-coding system in target repository
  Options: `--mode <mode>`, `--components <components>`
  Example: `sc install /path/to/project`

**`sc git-hooks`** - Git hooks management and installation
  Example: `sc git-hooks install`

**`sc git-smart`** - Smart git workflow utilities
  Options: `--branch <branch>`, `--verbose`
  Example: `sc git-smart --help`

**`sc deploy`** - Deploy project components
  Options: `--env <environment>`, `--service <service>`
  Example: `sc deploy --help`

### Feedback & Support

**`sc suggest`** - Instantly create GitHub issues with context
  Examples: 
  - `sc suggest "The kanban command is slow"`
  - `sc suggest bug "CLI crashes on empty directory"`
  - `sc suggest feature "Add dark mode support"`

### Help

**`sc help`** - Show comprehensive help
  Example: `sc help --help`

